ay it doesn&#39;t know which direction should move the cursor up, does that mean that the ball can rotate such that pushing up will move some amount of left/right/down?</p><span class="comment-actions secondary-text"><a class="comment-reply" target="_self" data-comment-id="1492900839082055475">Reply</a><span class="item-control blog-admin blog-admin pid-949554137"><a target="_self" href="https://www.blogger.com/delete-comment.g?blogID=5743520447405866726&amp;postID=1492900839082055475">Delete</a></span></span></div><div class="comment-replies"><div id="c1492900839082055475-rt" class="comment-thread inline-thread hidden"><span class="thread-toggle thread-expanded"><span class="thread-arrow"></span><span class="thread-count"><a target="_self">Replies</a></span></span><ol id="c1492900839082055475-ra" class="thread-chrome thread-expanded"><div></div><div id="c1492900839082055475-continue" class="continue"><a class="comment-reply" target="_self" data-comment-id="1492900839082055475">Reply</a></div></ol></div></div><div class="comment-replybox-single" id="c1492900839082055475-ce"></div></li></ol><div id="top-continue" class="continue"><a class="comment-reply" target="_self">Add comment</a></div><div class="comment-replybox-thread" id="top-ce"></div><div class="loadmore hidden" data-post-id="5639131155138198905"><a target="_self">Load more...</a></div></div>
